article.headline: Johns Hopkins 63, Navy 61
article.story:
BALTIMORE (AP) -- Terence Coppola scored with seven seconds
remaining to lift Johns Hopkins to a 63-61 win over Muhlenberg on
Saturday.

The Blue Jays (11-6, 8-3 Centennial Conference) were led by Eric
Toback, who scored 19 points.

For Muhlenberg (8-10, 5-6) were led by Jeff Stewart had his 11th
double-double of the season with 17 points and 12 rebounds.

Coppola's game-winner was set up moments earlier by a shot by
sophomore T.J. Valerio. Valerio got a pass from Toback, eluded a
defender, and nailed a 3-pointer and was fouled.

Valerio missed the free throw, but Toback grabbed the rebound,
which led to Coppola's game-winning basket.

Chase Licata threw up a desperation shot for Muhlenberg, but was
unsuccessful in the last seconds.

Muhlenberg had turned a 58-57 deficit into a 61-58 lead as a
basket by Jimmy O'Brien and two free throws by Stewart gave the
Mules some breathing room in the final minutes.

However, Valerio hit his 3-pointer just 12 seconds after
Stewart's free throws and Coppola's game-winner came shortly after.

A back-and-forth first half saw six lead-changes and two ties.

After Toback opened the scoring with a layup, the Mules went on
a 10-2 run, which saw four different Mules take part in the
scoring.
